ϵ(σ):=
\sigma  \sigma^{-1} = {\rm id}, 1 = \epsilon( {\rm id})= \epsilon(\sigma  \sigma^{-1} ) =\epsilon(\sigma)\epsilon(\sigma^{-1}) 
 \det A = \sum_\sigma {\epsilon(\sigma)} \prod_i A_{i,\sigma (i)} 
 \det A^T = \sum_\sigma {\epsilon(\sigma)} \prod_i A_{\sigma (i),i} \\\forall\sigma\ \  \prod_i A_{\sigma(i),i} = \prod_j A_{j,\sigma^{-1}(j)} 
\epsilon(\sigma)=\epsilon(\sigma^{-1})
\sigma \to \sigma^{-1}
 \det A^T = \sum_\sigma {\epsilon(\sigma^{-1})}\prod_j A_{j,\sigma^{-1}(j)} = \sum_\tau {\epsilon(\tau)}\prod_j A_{j,\tau(j)} = \det A 
